      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index benchmark comparison — FDA pump geometry",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against published FDA experimental data for the generic centrifugal blood pump at 5 operating points. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1.0 at all operating conditions. Mesh convergence confirmed at GCI < 2.3% for all cases. The accompanying UQ campaign (Latin hypercube, n=200 samples) demonstrated that the RH ranking across operating points was stable under geometric and boundary-condition perturbations, with coefficient of variation below 4% for the worst-case operating point identification."
